!item [Name:]
ØList Box Set Slider AÆ - Slider einer Listbox setzen.

!item [Opcode:]
175 (Sub-Opcode 0)

!item [Syntax:]
void lbox_set_asldr ( LIST_BOX *box, int16_t first, GRECT *rect );

or

void lbox_set_slider ( LIST_BOX *box, int16_t first, GRECT *rect );

!item [Description:]
Die Funktion positioniert den Slider-A einer Listbox. Es gilt:

!begin_xlist !short [Parameter]
!item [Parameter]
Meaning
!item [~]
~
!item [box]
Pointer to the list box structure
!item [first]
Index of the first visible entry
!item [rect]
Pointer to redraw rectangle or 0L
!end_xlist

(!B)Hint:(!b)
The contents of the list box will not be updated, 
so one may have to call lbox_update. 
If (!I)rect(!i) is 0L, then only the position of the slider objects will 
be altered, but the objects will not be drawn.

